Key Match Events: Pakistan recovered from 43 for four to post 185 for nine.
Shadab Khan (52 off 22) and Iftikhar Ahmed (51 off 35) smashed entertaining half-centuries.
South Africa could only score 108 for 9 while chasing a revised target of 142 from 14 overs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was rain-interrupted and Pakistan won by 33 runs under DLS method.
Shaheen Shah Afridi was the most successful Pakistan bowler with figures of 3/14.
Others: Brief Scores: Pakistan 185/9 in 20 overs (Shadab Khan 52, Iftikhar Ahmed 51; Anrich Nortje 4/41).
South Africa: 108 for 9 in 14 overs (D/L method) (Temba Bavuma 36; Shaheen Shah Afridi 3/14).
